### The Riemannian Hessian Under Reparametrization

Let \(\mathcal{L}:M\to\mathbb{R}\) be a function on a Riemannian manifold \(M\) with metric \(G\). The Riemannian Hessian \(\operatorname{Hess}\mathcal{L}\) of \(\mathcal{L}\) is defined in coordinates \(\theta\) by

\[\bm{H}_{ij}=\frac{\partial^{2}\mathcal{L}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{i}\partial \bm{\theta}^{j}}-\bm{\Gamma}_{ij}^{k}\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial\bm {\theta}^{k}},\] (6)

where \(\bm{\Gamma}_{ij}^{k}\) is the connection coefficient.

Under a change of coordinates \(\varphi:\bm{\theta}\mapsto\bm{\psi}\), we have \(\tilde{\mathcal{L}}=\mathcal{L}\circ\varphi^{-1}\) and

\[\tilde{\bm{\Gamma}}_{ij}^{k}=\bm{\Gamma}_{mn}^{o}\frac{\partial\bm{\psi}^{k}}{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{m}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}} \frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}+\frac{\partial^{2}\bm{ \theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}\frac{\partial\bm{\psi}^{k }}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}},\] (7)

where \(m\), \(n\), \(o\) are just dummy indices--present to express summations. Note that the transformation rule for \(\bm{\Gamma}_{ij}^{k}\) implies that it is _not_ a tensor--to be a tensor, there must not be the second term in the previous formula.

Using (7) and the standard chain & product rules to transform the partial derivatives in (6), we obtain the coordinate representation of the transformed Hessian \(\tilde{\mathcal{L}}\):

\[\tilde{\bm{H}}_{ij} =\frac{\partial^{2}(\mathcal{L}\circ\varphi^{-1})}{\partial\bm{ \psi}^{i}\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}-\tilde{\bm{\Gamma}}^{k}_{ij}\frac{\partial( \mathcal{L}\circ\varphi^{-1})}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{k}}\] (8) \[=\frac{\partial^{2}\mathcal{L}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{m}\partial \bm{\theta}^{n}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{m}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}}\frac{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}+\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial^{2}\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^ {i}\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}-\left(\bm{\Gamma}^{o}_{mn}\frac{\partial\bm{\psi}^{k }}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{m}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^ {i}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}+\frac{\partial^{2} \bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}\frac{\partial\bm {\psi}^{k}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\right)\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{k}}\] \[=\frac{\partial^{2}\mathcal{L}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{m}\partial \bm{\theta}^{n}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}}\frac{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}+\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial^{2}\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^ {i}\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}-\bm{\Gamma}^{o}_{mn}\frac{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j} \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{i}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{n}}{ \partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac {\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\psi}^{j}}\frac{\partial\mathcal{L}}{ \partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o }}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{ \theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial \bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac {\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\frac{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o }}{\partial\bm{\theta}^{o}}\f