We use the setting from the preceding section. Recall that \(\lambda\) is an eigenvalue of the linear map \(\bm{E}(\bm{\theta})=\bm{G}(\bm{\theta})^{-1}\bm{H}(\bm{\theta})\) on the tangent space at \(z\in\mathbb{R}^{d}\) that is represented \(\bm{\theta}\) if \(\bm{E}(\bm{\theta})\bm{v}=\lambda\bm{v}\) for an eigenvector \(\bm{v}\in T_{z}\mathbb{R}^{d}\). We shall show that \(\tilde{\lambda}\), the eigenvalue under under the reparametrization \(\varphi:\bm{\theta}\mapsto\bm{\psi}\), equals the original eigenvalue \(\lambda\).

